LA FORJA — LICENSING
====================

This repository is licensed in two parts. Read both.

  1. ITEM CONTENT  -> Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
  2. SOFTWARE      -> MIT License

Copyright (c) 2026 Manuel Peña Zúñiga (LA FORJA)


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. ITEM CONTENT — CC BY 4.0
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scope. The CC BY 4.0 license applies to the **original, team-authored
high-school/college mathematics item content** in this repository, and to
nothing else:

  - src/eval/smoke/dev/*.json      (labeled smoke set, dev split)
  - src/eval/smoke/holdout/*.json  (labeled smoke set, holdout split)
  - the seeded demo item in prisma/seed.ts

Each of those fixture files carries its own `_license` and `_attribution` fields.
Those per-file headers are authoritative for the file that contains them.

License text. The full legal code is published at:

  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

and the human-readable summary at:

  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

The canonical text at the first URL governs. In short: you may share and adapt
this item content for any purpose, including commercially, provided you give
appropriate credit, link to the license, and indicate whether changes were made.

Attribution line. When reusing the item content, credit it as:

  "LA FORJA item content by Manuel Peña Zúñiga (LA FORJA), licensed under
   CC BY 4.0 — https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"

Provenance and exclusions — these are hard rules, not preferences:

  - ORIGINALS ONLY. Every item in this repository is a high-school/college
    mathematics item written by the team for this project. No item, stem,
    passage, figure, answer key or taxonomy text from any exam body, ministry,
    publisher or third-party item bank appears here, in whole or in part.
  - CONTRIBUTOR CONTENT IS NOT COVERED. Items authored by testers or visitors of
    the public demo are private and ephemeral. They are never published and are
    never placed under this or any other license. No claim is made about the
    licensing of a future shared item bank.


